  <subsection xml:id="subsec-pyramid-volume-derivation">
    <title>Advanced: Derivation of Volume Formula</title>

    <p>Consider a cube with side length <m>x</m>, and so of volume <m>x^3</m>. Consider the center point in the cube, and connect it to all 8 corners,</p>

    <image width="50%">
      <latex-image>
        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1.2]
          % Cube vertices
          \coordinate (A) at (0,0);       % front-bottom-left
          \coordinate (B) at (3,0);       % front-bottom-right
          \coordinate (C) at (3,3);       % front-top-right
          \coordinate (D) at (0,3);       % front-top-left
          \coordinate (E) at (1.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-left
          \coordinate (F) at (4.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-right
          \coordinate (G) at (4.2,3.9);   % back-top-right
          \coordinate (H) at (1.2,3.9);   % back-top-left
          % Center
          \coordinate (O) at (2.1,1.95);
          % Back edges (dashed)
          \draw[dashed] (A) -- (E);
          \draw[dashed] (E) -- (F);
          \draw[dashed] (E) -- (H);
          % Front face
          \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;
          % Right face
          \draw[thick] (B) -- (F) -- (G) -- (C);
          % Top face
          \draw[thick] (D) -- (H) -- (G);
          % Lines from center to all corners
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (A);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (B);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (C);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (D);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (E);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (F);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (G);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (O) -- (H);
          % Center dot
          \fill[blue] (O) circle (2.5pt);
          \node[blue, below right] at (O) {center};
          % Side label
          \draw[&lt;-&gt;] (0,-0.4) -- (3,-0.4) node[midway, below] {$x$};
        \end{tikzpicture}
      </latex-image>
    </image>

    <p>This divides the cube into 6 identical pyramids of equal volume --- one pyramid for each face of the cube. Each pyramid has its base on a face of the cube and its apex at the center. Here is one of the 6 pyramids highlighted (the one whose base is the bottom face),</p>

    <image width="50%">
      <latex-image>
        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1.2]
          % Cube vertices
          \coordinate (A) at (0,0);       % front-bottom-left
          \coordinate (B) at (3,0);       % front-bottom-right
          \coordinate (C) at (3,3);       % front-top-right
          \coordinate (D) at (0,3);       % front-top-left
          \coordinate (E) at (1.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-left
          \coordinate (F) at (4.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-right
          \coordinate (G) at (4.2,3.9);   % back-top-right
          \coordinate (H) at (1.2,3.9);   % back-top-left
          % Center
          \coordinate (O) at (2.1,1.95);
          % Shade the bottom-face pyramid
          \fill[blue!20, opacity=0.6] (A) -- (B) -- (O) -- cycle;
          \fill[blue!12, opacity=0.6] (B) -- (F) -- (O) -- cycle;
          \fill[blue!10, opacity=0.6] (A) -- (E) -- (O) -- cycle;
          % Base fill
          \fill[blue!15, opacity=0.4] (A) -- (B) -- (F) -- (E) -- cycle;
          % Back edges (dashed)
          \draw[dashed] (A) -- (E);
          \draw[dashed] (E) -- (F);
          \draw[dashed] (E) -- (H);
          % Front face
          \draw[thick] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;
          % Right face
          \draw[thick] (B) -- (F) -- (G) -- (C);
          % Top face
          \draw[thick] (D) -- (H) -- (G);
          % Bottom face base of pyramid (blue)
          \draw[thick, blue] (A) -- (B);
          \draw[thick, blue] (B) -- (F);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (F) -- (E);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (E) -- (A);
          % Edges from bottom corners to center (the pyramid)
          \draw[thick, blue] (A) -- (O);
          \draw[thick, blue] (B) -- (O);
          \draw[thick, blue] (F) -- (O);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (E) -- (O);
          % Center dot
          \fill[blue] (O) circle (2.5pt);
          \node[blue, above left] at (O) {apex (center)};
          % Label
          \node[blue] at (2.1,-0.4) {base};
        \end{tikzpicture}
      </latex-image>
    </image>

    <p>Since the 6 pyramids fill the cube exactly,</p>
    <me>V_{\text{cube}} = x^3 = 6 V_{\text{pyramid}}</me>

    <p>Thus,</p>
    <me>V_{\text{pyramid}} = \frac{1}{6} x^3</me>

    <p>Each pyramid has a base that is a face of the cube (area <m>x^2</m>), and a height equal to half the side length (<m>\frac{x}{2}</m>), since the center is in the middle of the cube.</p>

    <image width="50%">
      <latex-image>
        \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1.2]
          % Cube vertices (same as above)
          \coordinate (A) at (0,0);       % front-bottom-left
          \coordinate (B) at (3,0);       % front-bottom-right
          \coordinate (C) at (3,3);       % front-top-right
          \coordinate (D) at (0,3);       % front-top-left
          \coordinate (E) at (1.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-left
          \coordinate (F) at (4.2,0.9);   % back-bottom-right
          \coordinate (G) at (4.2,3.9);   % back-top-right
          \coordinate (H) at (1.2,3.9);   % back-top-left
          % Center
          \coordinate (O) at (2.1,1.95);
          % Center of bottom face
          \coordinate (Obase) at (2.1,0.45);
          % Faint cube
          \draw[gray!60, dashed] (A) -- (E);
          \draw[gray!60, dashed] (E) -- (F);
          \draw[gray!60, dashed] (E) -- (H);
          \draw[gray!60] (A) -- (B) -- (C) -- (D) -- cycle;
          \draw[gray!60] (B) -- (F) -- (G) -- (C);
          \draw[gray!60] (D) -- (H) -- (G);
          % Shade the bottom-face pyramid
          \fill[blue!20, opacity=0.6] (A) -- (B) -- (O) -- cycle;
          \fill[blue!12, opacity=0.6] (B) -- (F) -- (O) -- cycle;
          \fill[blue!10, opacity=0.6] (A) -- (E) -- (O) -- cycle;
          \fill[blue!15, opacity=0.4] (A) -- (B) -- (F) -- (E) -- cycle;
          % Bottom face base of pyramid (blue)
          \draw[thick, blue] (A) -- (B);
          \draw[thick, blue] (B) -- (F);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (F) -- (E);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (E) -- (A);
          % Edges from bottom corners to center
          \draw[thick, blue] (A) -- (O);
          \draw[thick, blue] (B) -- (O);
          \draw[thick, blue] (F) -- (O);
          \draw[dashed, blue] (E) -- (O);
          % Center dot
          \fill[blue] (O) circle (2.5pt);
          % Height line
          \draw[dashed, thick] (Obase) -- (O);
          \draw (Obase) ++(0.2,0) -- ++(0,0.2) -- ++(-0.2,0);
          % Labels
          \draw[&lt;-&gt;] (0,-0.4) -- (3,-0.4) node[midway, below] {$x$};
          \node[left] at (2.1,1.3) {$\dfrac{x}{2}$};
          \node at (2.1, -1.0) {base area $= x^2$};
        \end{tikzpicture}
      </latex-image>
    </image>

    <p>Therefore,</p>
    <me>V_{\text{pyramid}} = \frac{1}{6} x^3 = \frac{1}{3} \cdot x^2 \cdot \frac{x}{2} = \frac{1}{3} A h</me>
  </subsection>

